- The address signifies a vibrant family lifestyle

Description:
Art Deco Classic with Corner Potential
In a convenient Coburg neighbourhood with easy access to everything that counts, this well-presented home occupies a sizeable allotment (corner of Ross Street) providing a lifestyle of immediate function along with a myriad of options for those looking to renovate, rebuild or redevelop. Current floorplan comprises two bedrooms (large master) plus study/3rd bedroom, central bathroom and separate WC, front lounge and adjoining dining area through to the kitchen/meals and rear sunroom. Features of the home include ducted heating and evaporative cooling, high Art Deco ceilings, solar power, large laundry, plus a private backyard with undercover patio and remote-control garage via Ross Street. Enviable urban ease, it's walking distance to Batman Station and Sydney Road trams, also close to primary and secondary schools, Coburg Lake Reserve as well as popular cafes and vibrant shopping precincts. Internal house size approx. 126sqm Agent: Nelson Alexander Pty Ltd

Description:
Timeless Charm, Coburg Convenience
Irresistible charm and a coveted Coburg location combine to deliver a family home that's certain to generate wide appeal.
With St Fidelis and Coburg West primary schools a short walk from the front door, the location is ideal for the growing family or the young couple with an eye on the future. Factor in the swift access to the No.58 tram, Moreland train station, the popular Sydney Road shopping and dining strip, Citylink and scenic parkland and it's understandable why this location also represents a solid blue-chip investment.
Polished timber floorboards flow beneath the towering high ceilings that are gifts of a bygone era, while zoned living sees three generous-sized bedrooms (master with period fireplace) and a bright family bathroom secluded from the central open-plan living/dining area and large updated kitchen equipped with generous bench space and a 600mm upright cooker.
Presented in pristine condition, there's scope to further enhance the interior with a modern touch, while the blank canvas nature of the low-maintenance backyard will also encourage you to create something special.
Featuring rear lane access, gas heating, split-system heating/cooling and a large shed with kitchenette and laundry, make your presence felt in desirable Coburg.

Description:
Brand New With No Body Corporate Fees!
Street frontage, two bedroom town home with City views has been meticulously built and finished in quiet tree lined street. Stroll to both Melville and Sydney Roads eateries and shopping precincts, trams and Moreland Rail Station.
Accommodation includes:
• Two spacious bedrooms with fitted wardrobes
• Central / ensuite bathroom
• European laundry
• Sunny courtyard
Upstairs:
• Spacious open plan living to furnish at will, opening to entertainers balcony with City Views
• Fully equipped chefs kitchen with stone bench tops and pantry
• Powder room
Featuring: quality floor coverings, polished timber floors, split system heating and cooling throughout, alarm system, ducted vacuum throughout, remote garage with 2nd car space in front of garage.
This beautiful home is offered for immediate living in prestigious location surrounded by quality homes , John Fawkner Hospital and easy access to City Link and Tullamarine Freeways.

Description:
Light and Style with Impressive Proportions
Modern low-maintenance perfection, this near-new townhouse is sure to make a lasting impression with its intelligent design, long list of features and coveted Coburg location for outstanding urban ease. Complete with its own street frontage, the home's feature-packed interior comprises two large bedrooms (both with full-height robes) and two deluxe bathrooms (one on each level) both with stone-top vanities and floor-to-ceiling tiles. Add to this a spacious open-plan living/dining area complemented by a front balcony and stacker doors to private rear fully-decked terrace complete with pergola and vertical garden. Other highlights include a stone-bench kitchen with soft-close cabinetry and Bosch dishwasher, study alcove with integrated workstation along with split-system heating/cooling, premium 100% wool carpets and engineered oak floors, efficient LED lighting and 2.7m square-set ceilings throughout, plus European laundry and oversized single garage/workshop (r/c). Walking distance to Melville Road & Sydney Rd trams, local buses, Coburg West and St Fidelis primary schools, it's close to Moreland & Strathmore Stations and shopping precinct as well as easy access to Citylink/Tullamarine Freeway.
Insights: 2/260 Reynard Street, Coburg VIC 3058 was last sold in 2019 and 58 other 2 bedroom house in Coburg have recently been sold.

Description:
Exciting Options Ahead!
In need of renovation and in a prized location with immediate access to the best of Coburg, this freestanding Edwardian home provides all the necessary ingredients for a significant extension and stunning renovation (STCA). Current floorplan includes an entrance hallway accessing two large bedrooms and wide central lounge, plus a functional bathroom and kitchen/meals area. Step outside to discover a substantial north-facing backyard with plenty of room to expand. South of Bell Street with the area's key lifestyle attractions at your fingertips, it's walking distance to trains and trams, local shops and major supermarkets, an endless choice of cafes and restaurants as well as easy access to local parks and popular primary schools.

Description:
A perfect start in a perfect location
Do not miss the fantastic opportunity to purchase this ground floor, renovated one bedroom apartment, conveniently located close to Sydney Road and all amenities. Featuring a spacious open plan kitchen and lounge with floating floor. Fresh and bright bedroom with built in robes and brand new carpet, plus ensuite bathroom. One car space on title, with multiple visitor spots and modern laundry facilities completes the package. Perfectly situated close to trams, trains and buses, Sydney road boutiques, cafes, restaurants and shopping. There is nothing to do except move in or rent out and benefit from the exceptional convenience!
